        <body>
            <div class="Section1">
                <div class="header">
                    <div>
                        <apex:image url="https://cvest.my.salesforce.com/servlet/servlet.ImageServer?id=0150a000001fqte&oid=00Dj0000000L4sC" />
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="footer">
                    <div></div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="content">
                <p style="font-family: Times; font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.3;  page-break-inside:avoid;">
                    <!-- <apex:outputText value="{!TEXT(MONTH(Opportunity.Term_Sheet_Issued__c)) & '/' & TEXT(DAY(Opportunity.Term_Sheet_Issued__c)) & '/' & TEXT(YEAR(Opportunity.Term_Sheet_Issued__c))}" /> -->
                    <apex:outputText value=" {0,date, MMMM d',' yyyy}">
                        <apex:param value="{! DATE(todayYear, todayMonth, todayDay)}" /></apex:outputText>
                </p>
                <p style="font-family: Times; font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.3;  page-break-inside:avoid;">
                    
                    <apex:outputField value="{!Opportunity.Account.BillingStreet}" />
                    <br />
                    <apex:outputText value="{!Opportunity.Account.BillingCity}, " />
                    <apex:outputText value="{!Opportunity.Account.Billing_State_Code__c} " rendered="{!NOT (ISBLANK(Opportunity.Account.BillingState))}"
                                     />
                    <apex:outputText value="{!Opportunity.Account.BillingPostalCode}" />
                    <br />
                    
                    <span style="{!IF(NOT(Opportunity.Account.BillingCountry == 'United States'), 'page-break-inside:avoid;', 'display:none;')}">
                        <apex:outputText value="{!Opportunity.Account.BillingCountry}" rendered="{!NOT(Opportunity.Account.BillingCountry == 'United States')}"
                                         />
                        <br />
                    </span>
                    <apex:outputText value="{!'Attention: ' & Opportunity.Primary_Contact__c } " /> ("
                    <strong>Sponsor</strong>")
                </p>
                <p style="{!IF(includeCOBroker = true, 'page-break-inside:avoid;', 'display:none;')}">
                    <span style="font-family: Times; font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.3;  page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        C/O:
                        <apex:outputText value=" {!Opportunity.Referral_Source_Contact__r.Name} " /> -
                        <apex:outputText value=" {!Opportunity.Referral_Source__r.Name}" />
                    </span>
                </p>
                <p style="font-family: Times; font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.3;  page-break-inside:avoid;">
                    <strong>[USE FOR SINGLE FAMILY/TOWNHOME PROJECTS]</strong>
                    <apex:outputText value=" ${0,number} ">
                        <apex:param value="{!Opportunity.Loan_Size__c}" />
                    </apex:outputText> Construction Loan Proposal to finance the the acquisition/refinancing and construction of [[XXX] Residential Units, defined below, each on a subdivided residential lot located at {!allProperties[0].Name} (the <strong>"Property"</strong>)
                    
                </p>
                
                <p style="font-family: Times; font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.3;  page-break-inside:avoid;">
                    <strong>[USE FOR MULTIFAMILY PROJECTS]</strong>
                    <apex:outputText value=" ${0,number} ">
                        <apex:param value="{!Opportunity.Loan_Size__c}" />
                    </apex:outputText> <strong>[USE FOR MULTIFAMILY PROJECTS]</strong>$[XXX] Construction Loan Proposal to finance the acquisition/refinancing and construction of a multifamily apartment project to be comprised of [XXX] Residential Units (defined below located at [_____________] (the "Property")
                    
                </p>
                
                <p style="font-family: Times; font-size: 11pt; line-height: 1.3;  page-break-inside:avoid;">
                    <apex:outputText value="{! 'Dear ' & Opportunity.Contact__r.FirstName}" />:
                </p>
                
                <p class="paragraph">
                    CoreVest American Finance Lender LLC or an affiliated entity ("<strong>Lender"</strong>) is pleased to present this summary proposal to provide a secured construction loan to finance the acquisition/refinancing of the Property (exclusive of any to-be demolished existing improvements) and Eligible Project Costs (defined below) for the vertical construction of the Residential Units.  As further set forth below, this proposal is for discussion purposes only and is neither an expressed nor implied commitment to provide any financing or to provide or purchase any loans or securities in connection with the transactions contemplated hereby. 
                </p>
                
                <table style="table-layout: fixed; width:95vw;" cellspacing="0">
                    <colgroup>
                        <col class="short" />
                        <col class="long" />
                    </colgroup>
                    
                    <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                            Borrower:
                        </td>
                        <td class="row-description">
                            A bankruptcy-remote, single-purpose limited liability company (LLC) acceptable to Lender.  The LLC will include <mark> <apex:outputText value="{!Opportunity.Borrower_Entity__r.Name}"/> </mark> (<strong>"Sponsor"</strong>) or an affiliate of Sponsor approved by Lender as an equity owner and as managing member or manager.  Lender reserves the right to approve any other equity owners and/or managers in the LLC prior to closing, and no transfers, pledges or assignments of direct or indirect equity interests shall be permitted except as noted in the below Section entitled "No Transfers".  If an equity pledge is required, Borrower must be a single member Delaware limited liability company, with the form of the LLC Agreement in form and substance acceptable to Lender and its counsel.
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                    
                    <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                            Guarantor:  
                        </td>
                        <td class="row-description">
                            The undersigned "Sponsor" and/or such individuals or entities acceptable to Lender following due diligence.
                        </td>
                        
                    </tr>
                    
                    <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                            Pledgor:    
                        </td>
                        <td class="row-description">
                            A bankruptcy remote, Delaware limited liability company, acceptable to Lender following due diligence, which shall be the sole member of Borrower. <mark>[REPLACE WITH "NOT REQUIRED" IF NO EQUITY PLEDGE]</mark>
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                    
                    <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                            Net Worth and 
                            Liquidity
                            Requirement:
                        </td>
                        <td class="row-description">
                            Prior to Loan closing the Guarantor(s) shall evidence, on a combined basis if more than one Guarantor, a minimum net worth of 100% of the Maximum Loan Amount and minimum aggregate liquidity of 10% of the Maximum Loan Amount based on readily marketable securities and bank accounts within the United States of America.  Following Loan closing these requirements must be maintained at all times and shall be tested quarterly based on unaudited compiled financial statements with supporting current bank/brokerage account statements.
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                    
                    <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                            Property:
                        </td>
                        <td class="row-description">
                            <p>[XXX] acres of unimproved land comprised of <mark>[XXX]</mark> legally subdivided residential lot(s) (each a <strong>"Residential Lot"</strong>) each of which is a Finished Lot(s) located at the address set forth above to be improved with <mark>[XXX]</mark> residential dwelling units (each a <strong>"Residential Unit"</strong> and collectively, together with any related improvements included in the Final Plans <strong><mark>[**List any specific improvements such as a clubhouse, parking garage, pool and other amenities], the "Improvements").  The Improvements shall include [**list Project type (e.g. single family homes/townhomes, multifamily apartment building(s) and square footage and unit mix # of 1 bed, 2 bed 3, bed etc.]</mark></strong> (unit mix may change prior to Loan closing) pursuant to Final Plans, Construction Documents (defined below) and a construction budget, detailing by line item total eligible project costs, as approved by Lender prior to the closing of the Loan, and otherwise in accordance with the terms and conditions to be set forth in the loan documents (as approved by Lender, the <strong>"Budget"</strong>).  Borrower's preliminary proposed budget submitted to Lender for review and approval during the due diligence period is attached hereto as <strong><u>Exhibit B.</u></strong>  No Property may at any time be occupied by Borrower, Guarantor or any interest owner, or affiliate or relative thereof. <strong>[TO BE CONFIRMED PROPERTY AND IF APPLICABLE, THE RESIDENTIAL LOTS, ARE SUBDIVIDED AND NO HORIZONTAL OR OFF-SITE IMPROVEMENTS]</strong></p>
                            <p><strong>"Finished Lot"</strong> means the Property, and if applicable, each Residential Lot, is a separate legal parcel and if multiple Residential Lots, all of such Residential Lots are contiguous, excepting any existing public roads, (b) all off-site construction and infrastructure necessary to permit construction of the Improvements on the Property and issuance of permanent certificates of occupancy upon Completion has been completed in accordance with all legal requirements, (c) all utilities have been installed and are available to the Property, and each Residential Lot located with the Property, and (d) building permits may be issued and construction commenced upon payment of the building permit fees and otherwise without satisfaction of any further material conditions.</p>
                            
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                    
                    <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                            Loan Purpose:   
                        </td>
                        <td class="row-description">
                            Refinancing or acquisition of the Property and financing of a portion of the Eligible Project Costs for construction of the Improvements and payment of interest on the Loan as described below.
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                    
                    <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                            Closing:    
                        </td>
                        <td class="row-description">
                            Anticipated to be 45 days from the execution of this Loan Proposal (provided timely delivery of Due Diligence).
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                    
                    <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                            Maximum Loan
                            Amount/ Advances:
                        </td>
                        <td class="row-description">
                            <p>Maximum Loan Amount of <mark><apex:outputText value=" ${0,number} "><apex:outputText value="{!Opportunity.Loan_Size__c}" /></apex:outputText></mark>, subject to confirmation and determined by Lender as follows: the Maximum Loan Amount will be the lesser of: (a) <mark>[XXX]</mark>% of the "As-Stabilized" market value of the Property as determined by Lender based on an appraisal of the Property prepared by an appraiser selected by Lender and in form and scope acceptable to Lender (<strong>"As-Stabilized Value"</strong>) and (b) <mark>[XXX]</mark>% of an amount equal to (i) the Third Party Purchase Price paid for the Property as determined by Lender plus (ii)  the total project costs necessary to achieve Completion of the Improvements on the Property in the amount to be set forth in the Budget less any such project costs that may have been incurred and paid for by Borrower prior to Loan closing to the extent verified as such by Lender in the amount set forth in the Budget which may be either credited to Borrower's [Initial] Equity Contribution or reimbursed to Borrower as part of the Initial Advance (discussed below) plus (iii)  the Interest Allocation discussed below, in the amount set forth in the Budget (the project costs described in clauses (b)(ii) and (iii) above are collectively referred to as the, <strong>"Eligible Project Costs"</strong>) and as more fully described in the loan documents. As used herein, <strong>"Third Party Purchase Price"</strong> means the purchase price paid by Borrower or an affiliate of Borrower or Sponsor for the Property to a third party seller who is not related to or affiliated with Borrower or Sponsor pursuant to a written purchase and sale agreement. </p>
                            <p>The initial advance to be disbursed on the Closing Date for financing the acquisition or refinancing of the Property which  may include reimbursement of any project costs incurred and paid for in full by Borrower prior to Loan closing to the extent such paid project costs are verified as such by Lender prior to Loan closing and have not been credited to Borrower's [Initial] Equity Contribution (the <strong>"Initial Advance"</strong>) is anticipated to be the lesser of (a) [<mark>XXX</mark>]% of the Third Party Purchase Price paid for the Property and (b)[<mark>XXX</mark>]% of the "As-Is" appraised value as determined by Lender based on the appraisal of the Property prepared by an appraiser selected by Lender and in form and scope acceptable to Lender (<strong>"As-Is Value"</strong>). The remaining portion of the Maximum Loan Amount (the <strong>"Construction Loan Proceeds"</strong>) will be advanced in multiple advances (each an "Advance") to pay for Eligible Project Costs per the Budget. As used herein, <strong>"Construction Advance"</strong> means an Advance to pay for Eligible Project Costs other than Advances from the Interest Allocation to pay interest on the Loan. The Construction Loan Proceeds are estimated to be $[<mark>XXX</mark>] subject to confirmation by Lender. See <strong>Exhibit A</strong> - "Sources and Uses.</p>
                            
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                    
                    <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                            Borrower
                            Equity Contribution:
                        </td>
                        <td class="row-description">
                            <p>[USE IF NO ADDITIONAL EQUITY] an estimated [$<mark>XXX</mark>] of invested equity capital, inclusive of cash and land equity, to be evidenced at Loan closing (<strong> "Borrower's Equity Contribution" </strong>), subject to confirmation as determined by Lender prior to Loan Closing that the Construction Loan Proceeds are not less than Eligible Project Costs.]</p>
                            <p>[USE IF ADDITIONAL EQUITY REQUIRED] an estimated $[<mark>XXX</mark>] of invested equity capital, inclusive of cash and land equity, to be evidenced at Loan closing (<strong> "Borrower's Initial Equity Contribution" </strong>) at Loan Closing, subject to Lender confirmation prior to Loan Closing.</p>
                            <p>Following Loan Closing, an additional estimated $[<mark>XXX</mark>] of equity capital to be fully invested by Borrower towards Eligible Project Costs prior to and as a condition to the disbursement of any Construction Advance under the Loan (<strong>"Borrower's Additional Equity Contribution"</strong>), subject to confirmation as determined by Lender prior to Loan Closing that the Construction Loan Proceeds plus Borrower's Additional Equity Contribution are not less than Eligible Project Costs.  Before any further Construction Advance is made, Borrower shall be required to provide evidence to Lender that it has paid (from sources other than Advances) Eligible Project Costs in an amount equal to Borrower's Additional Equity Contribution. Evidence that Borrower's Additional Equity Contribution shall be by way of submitting to Lender a Draw Package (defined below). The outside date for Borrower to fully invest Borrower's Additional Equity Contribution to be determined by Lender during the due diligence period and prior to Loan Closing.</p>
                            
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                    
                    <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                            Loan Term:  
                        </td>
                        <td class="row-description">
                            [<mark>XXX</mark>] months [<mark>INSERT IF EXTENSION OPTION</mark> "Initial Stated Maturity Date"]
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                    
                    <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                            Extension Option:
                            </td>
                                                    <td class="row-description">

                        <span style="{!IF(Opportunity.LOC_Extension__c = '6 months, 50bps', 'page-break-inside:avoid;', 'display:none;')}">
                            [<mark>1 six (6)</mark>] month extension option subject to extension requirements below.][REPLACE WITH "NONE" IF NO EXTENSION OPTION]
                        </span>
                        <span style="{!IF(Opportunity.LOC_Extension__c = 'None' , 'page-break-inside:avoid;', 'display:none;')}">
                        None
                        </span>
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                    
                    <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                            Interest Rate:
                        </td>
                        <td class="row-description">
                            <p>The Loan will bear interest at a floating rate per annum equal to Term SOFR plus [<mark>XXX</mark>]% (<strong>"Interest Rate"</strong>), adjusted monthly and provided Term SOFR shall not be less than the Floor. Interest will be paid monthly in arrears on the tenth day of each calendar month for accrued interest for the preceding calendar month (each an <strong>"Interest Accrual Period"</strong>").  Interest will be calculated based on a 360-day year and the actual number of days elapsed (Actual/360) and will accrue on any unpaid principal balance. As used herein, the following terms shall have the meanings set forth below:</p>
                            <p><strong> "Floor" </strong>  means [<mark>XXX</mark>]% per annum.</p>
                            <p><strong>"Interest Adjustment Date"</strong>  means, for the initial Interest Accrual Period, the date that is two U.S. Government Securities Business Days prior to the first day of the calendar month in which the Closing Date occurs, and for any subsequent Interest Accrual Period, the date that is two U.S. Government Securities Business Days prior to the first day of such Interest Accrual Period.</p>
                            <p><strong> "SOFR" </strong>  means a rate equal to the secured overnight financing rate as administered by the Federal Reserve Bank of New York (or a successor administrator of the secured overnight financing rate).</p>
                            <p><strong> "Term SOFR" </strong>  means, for any Interest Accrual Period, the rate per annum equal to the forward-looking term rate based on SOFR for a one-month tenor as of the Interest Adjustment Date, as published by the CME Group Benchmark Administration Limited (or a successor administrator of such rate), as determined by Lender; provided that if as of 5:00 p.m. U.S. Central Time on the Interest Adjustment Date Term SOFR has not been published, then Term SOFR shall mean such rate as of the first U.S. Government Securities Business Day preceding the Interest Adjustment Date for which a Term SOFR was published so long as such first preceding U.S. Government Securities Business Day is not more than three U.S. Government Securities Business Days prior to the Interest Adjustment Date. </p>
                            <p><strong> "U.S. Government Securities Business Day" </strong>  means any day except for (i) a Saturday, (ii) a Sunday or (iii) a day on which the Securities Industry and Financial Markets Association recommends that the fixed income departments of its members be closed for the entire day for purposes of trading in United States government securities.</p>
                            
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                    
                    <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                            Amortization:
                        </td>
                        <td class="row-description">
                            Interest Only
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                    
                    <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                            Origination Fee:    
                        </td>
                        <td class="row-description">
                            <mark><apex:outputText value="{!Opportunity.Requested_Origination_Fee__c}" />%</mark>% of the Maximum Loan Amount payable at Closing, which fee shall be fully earned and non-refundable to Borrower.
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                    
                    <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                            Construction
                            Monitoring Fee:
                        </td>
                        <td class="row-description">
                            $[<mark>1,000</mark>] per Construction Advance payable to Lender as a condition to each Construction Advance.
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                    
                    <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                            Exit Fee:
                        </td>
                        <td class="row-description">
                             <span style="{!IF(Opportunity.Partial_Release__c   != null , 'page-break-inside:avoid;', 'display:none;')}">
                            [USE IF NO PARTIAL RELEASES][<mark>                         <apex:outputText value="{!Opportunity.Exit_Fee__c}" />
</mark>]% of the Maximum Loan Amount, which shall be due and payable in full upon the earlier of (a) the maturity date of the Loan, and (b) the date the Loan is repaid in full, provided that the Exit Fee will be waived if the Loan is repaid in full with a permanent term loan from Lender or Lender's affiliate.][or replace with NONE if no Exit Fee]
                       </span>
                            <span style="{!IF(Opportunity.Exit_Fee__c = null , 'page-break-inside:avoid;', 'display:none;')}">
None                       </span>
                       
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                    
                    <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                            Property Exit Fee:
                        </td>
                        <td class="row-description">
                            <p>[USE IF PARTIAL RELEASES][<mark>XXX</mark>]% of 1/[<mark>total number of Residential Units</mark>] of the Maximum Loan Amount for each Residential Unit (as may be adjusted by Lender during Lender's due diligence based on the Residential Unit composition (e.g., unit size and type), per Release Property appraised value or other pertinent factors as determined by Lender), which shall be due and payable in full upon the earlier of (a) the maturity date of the Loan, (b) the date the Loan is repaid in full, or (c) or in connection with the release of a Release Property and satisfaction of the Property Release conditions for such Release Property, provided that the Property Exit Fee will be waived for any Release Property that is refinanced with a permanent term loan from Lender or Lender's affiliate.] </p>
                        </td>
                    </tr>   
                    
                    <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                            Extension Fee:
                        </td>
                        <td class="row-description">
                        <span style="{!IF(Opportunity.Partial_Release__c   = null , 'page-break-inside:avoid;', 'display:none;')}">
[<mark>XXX</mark>]% of the [USE IF NO PARTIAL RELEASES]Maximum Loan Amount. 
</span>
                            <span style="{!IF(Opportunity.Partial_Release__c   != null , 'page-break-inside:avoid;', 'display:none;')}">

[USE IF PARTIAL RELEASES]outstanding principal balance of the Loan on the Initial Stated Maturity Date.]
                                             </span>
 
                        </td>
                    </tr>   
                    
                    <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                            Extension Option 
                            Requirements: 
                            
                        </td>
                        <td class="row-description">
                            <p class ="paragraph">a) No default or event of default has occurred and is then continuing,</p>
                            <p class ="paragraph">b) Borrower shall have delivered to Lender written notice requesting such extension at least 60 days but no more than 180 days prior to the stated maturity date, </p>
                            <p class ="paragraph">c) Borrower shall have paid Lender the Extension Fee on or before the Initial Stated Maturity Date; </p>
                            <p class ="paragraph">d) The Loan must be in balance through extended maturity with Borrower depositing necessary Balancing Funds prior to the Initial Stated Maturity Date (see "Loan in Balance" below); </p>
                            <p class ="paragraph"> (e) Completion of all of the Improvements, including issuance of a permanent certificate of occupancy for each Residential Unit and if applicable, dedication and acceptance of all public on and offsite improvements has occurred; </p>
                            <p class ="paragraph"> (f) An As-Is LTV ratio of no greater than [XX]%[INSERT THE STABILIZED LTV % IN ABOVE SECTION ENTITLED MAXIMUM LOAN AMOUNT] as tested by an updated current appraisal; </p>
                            <p class ="paragraph"> (g) Borrower shall have provided evidence satisfactory to Lender that at least [<strong>85</strong>]% of the Residential Units are occupied by Eligible Tenants pursuant to Eligible Leases as of the Initial Stated Maturity Date; and</p>
                            <p class ="paragraph"> (h) There shall have been no material adverse change in the financial condition of Guarantor that would materially and adversely affect Guarantor's ability to perform its obligations under the Loan Documents, as determined by Lender, and Guarantor shall have delivered to Lender a Compliance Certificate dated as of the Initial Stated Maturity Date, with all supporting documentation, evidencing Guarantor is in compliance with Guarantor's  minimum liquidity and net worth covenants.[IF NO EXTENSION OPTION, DELETE (a)-(h) TEXT AND REPLACE WITH N/A] </p>
                            
                            
                        </td>
                    </tr>  
                    
                    <tr style="page-break-inside:avoid;">
                        <td class="row-title">
                            Outside
                            Completion Date: 
                        </td>
                        <td class="row-description">
                            The Improvements must be Completed no later than the date that is [<mark>XXX</mark>] months following the closing of the Loan (<strong>"Outside Completion Date"</strong>).
                        </td>
                    </tr>  
                    
